phase2.explanation:
You didn't check if the read succeeded!

**The fix:**
```cpp
if (file >> value) {
    std::cout << "Value: " << value << std::endl;
} else {
    std::cout << "Failed to read value!" << std::endl;
}
```

**PlusPlus-chan says:**
"Always check if reads succeed. Data might be missing or corrupted."

